summary_generated: Veterans' Education and Training Act of 1994 - Makes technical and conforming amendments to Federal provisions concerning: (1) active duty training; (2) the reserve program; (3) training and rehabilitation for veterans with service-connected disabilities; (4) alternative teacher certification programs; (5) education outside the United States; (6) correspondence courses; and (7) approval of programs of education.

Know Before You Fly Act (Sec. 2) This bill makes it an unfair or deceptive practice for any air carrier, foreign air carrier, or ticket agent to fail to include, in an internet fare quotation for a specific itinerary in air transportation selected by a consumer, a clear statement that additional fees for checked baggage and carry-on baggage may apply, along with a prominent link from that internet website page directly to a list of all such fees. The information provided by a covered air carrier shall identify each air carrier and foreign air carrier with which it will arrange air transportation
predicted_summary: Know Before You Fly Act - Amends the Federal Aviation Act to prohibit: (1) an unfair or deceptive practice to include, in an internet fare quotation for a specific itinerary in air transportation selected by a consumer, a clear and prominent statement that additional fees for checked baggage and carry-on baggage may apply, along with a prominent link from that internet website page directly to a list of all such fees. (2) Nothing in this Act may be construed to derogate or limit any responsibilities of an Air carrier, foreign air carrier, or ticket agent under section 399.85 of title 14, Code of Federal Regulations, or any successor provision.Authorizes a covered air carrier to: (1) provide for hotel accommodations; (2) arrange for air transportation on another carrier or foreign air carrier; (3) provide meal vouchers; (4) provide adequate air transportation to the passenger's destination; and (5) provide necessary sleeping facilities, food, and water.Authorizes the Administrator of the Federal Aviation Administration to: (1) receive and analyze reports involving fumes in the air conditioning and pressurization systems of aircraft operated under this Act's provisions.Requires the head of the Office designated under this Act to report annually on: (1) the number of reports received; (2) the disposition of reports; and (3) the status of any corrective actions identified.

summary_generated: Transparency and Accountability of Failed Exchanges Act - Amends the Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act to require a state that is awarded a grant to establish an American Health Benefit Exchange (a health insurance exchange created under such Act) that terminates the operation of such Exchange or otherwise transfers the operation of it to an entity other than such state to: (1) submit to Congress and the Secretary of Health and Human Services (HHS) a report containing the results of an audit of how amounts awarded to it pursuant to the grant were used; and (2) within 30 days after such termination or transfer, rescind any unobligated amounts awarded to it pursuant to the grant and require the state to provide to the Administrator of General Services any property acquired with such amounts, as well as submit to Congress and the Secretary a record of the provision of such property to the Administrator. Requires funds rescinded to be retained in the general fund of the Treasury for federal budget deficit reduction and allows the Administrator to dispose of any property obtained through a public auction for cash and for not less than its fair market value, as determined by the Administrator. Provides that such property shall not be subject to certain property disposal requirements.
